A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Subpart 2A of Part 3 of Article 7 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of
2 Georgia Annotated, relating to the needs based financial aid program, so as to revise the
3 definition of "eligible student"; to extend an automatic repealer; to provide for related
4 matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Subpart 2A of Part 3 of Article 7 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
8 Annotated, relating to the needs based financial aid program, is amended by revising
9 paragraph (1) of Code Section 20-3-360, relating to definitions, as follows:
10 "(1) 'Eligible student' means a person:
11 (A) Whose family income is considered economically disadvantaged, based on criteria
12 established by the commission, or who has a financial aid gap;
13 (B) Who meets any academic or other standards established by the commission;
14 (C) Who is eligible for a scholarship or grant pursuant to Code Section 20-3-519.1;
15 (D) Who has completed the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA); and
16 (E) Who has completed:
